It'll take them a while to get here.

259
00:14:42,598 --> 00:14:44,570
The nearest ER is on the mainland.

260
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:47,787
Huh?

261
00:14:56,654 --> 00:14:58,202
Hey, Teacher Man.

262
00:14:58,514 --> 00:15:01,660
I'd say your students are in a bad way right about now.

263
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:03,817
Uh. And who is this?

264
00:15:03,973 --> 00:15:05,465
Oh, no! Ritsu!

265
00:15:05,656 --> 00:15:06,906
Take it easy, friend.

266
00:15:06,931 --> 00:15:09,161
There's no need for you to know who I am.

267
00:15:10,129 --> 00:15:14,642
Just know your squad of snot-nosed punks
aren't the only ones tryin' to hit their mark.

268
00:15:14,973 --> 00:15:17,639
You're telling me you're responsible for making them sick?

269
00:15:18,551 --> 00:15:19,638
You're good.

270
00:15:20,114 --> 00:15:22,586
But they're a hell of a lot more than sick.

271
00:15:23,125 --> 00:15:26,333
Their bodies are hosting a lab-manufactured virus.

272
00:15:26,473 --> 00:15:28,764
Incubation period and specific symptoms vary,

273
00:15:28,848 --> 00:15:31,639
but the end result is the same. After about a week,

274
00:15:31,723 --> 00:15:34,409
cells begin to rupture and vital organs become jelly.

275
00:15:35,441 --> 00:15:38,230
The only known antidote is also lab-made.

276
00:15:38,701 --> 00:15:41,147
Lucky for you, I am its sole possessor.

277
00:15:41,758 --> 00:15:43,537
Trouble is, I'm lazy.

278
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:46,620
If you want it, you're gonna
have to come get it yourselves.

279
00:15:47,215 --> 00:15:50,155
There's a hotel on top of this island's highest peak.

280
00:15:50,337 --> 00:15:52,984
Bring me your precious cargo, and we'll chat.

281
00:15:54,336 --> 00:15:57,431
Top floor, within the hour. No tricks.

282
00:15:57,514 --> 00:15:59,348
And because you seem like the sort of man

283
00:15:59,431 --> 00:16:01,995
I wouldn't want to tangle with, send proxies.

284
00:16:02,387 --> 00:16:03,384
Two students.

285
00:16:03,447 --> 00:16:05,370
The shortest boy and shortest girl.

286
00:16:05,773 --> 00:16:08,253
Out of whoever's still standing, of course.

287
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:15,079
There's a concierge desk across from the
elevators, have them go there. If all goes well,

288
00:16:15,139 --> 00:16:17,348
you'll have the antidote, and I'll have the bounty.

289
00:16:17,462 --> 00:16:20,005
Now, this should go without saying,

290
00:16:20,098 --> 00:16:23,389
but contact outside help or show up late, and boom.

291
00:16:23,532 --> 00:16:25,323
The antidote goes bye-bye.

292
00:16:25,372 --> 00:16:26,624
The infected die.

293
00:16:28,561 --> 00:16:34,172
Hey, you guys were fantastic. With the target immobilized,
the hard part's done. I can't thank you enough.

294
00:16:34,487 --> 00:16:37,498
Lady luck is definitely smiling down on our cause.

295
00:16:43,061 --> 00:16:43,712
Damn it!

296
00:16:43,997 --> 00:16:47,009
Of all the times for some
psychotic bastard to sabotage us!

297
00:16:53,625 --> 00:16:56,208
Mr. Karasuma, I'm afraid they're not cooperating.

298
00:16:56,406 --> 00:16:59,281
Even when we play the government
card, the hotel owners maintain

299
00:16:59,306 --> 00:17:01,295
they have the right to protect their guests' identity.

300
00:17:01,621 --> 00:17:02,494
Naturally.

301
00:17:02,598 --> 00:17:03,533
Intolerable!

302
00:17:03,783 --> 00:17:09,151
But not surprising. The resort our mystery man chose
is a known site for all manner of illegal operations.

303
00:17:09,295 --> 00:17:13,212
Remote, shady history. It bares all the
trappings of an ideal rendezvous point.

304
00:17:13,621 --> 00:17:16,037
The owners have connections
with Higher Ups in the government.

305
00:17:16,211 --> 00:17:18,050
Law enforcement knows to leave it alone.

306
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:22,764
So basically there's no way of knowing
who the prick is before we meet him.

307
00:17:22,871 --> 00:17:26,051
Ah! Are we really gonna take this psycho's word for it?

308
00:17:26,246 --> 00:17:29,317
If he's bullshitting us about
the antidote, we're all gonna die!

309
00:17:29,514 --> 00:17:31,446
Calm down, dude, it's fine.

310
00:17:31,723 --> 00:17:34,441
We came here to be killers, not victims, remember?

311
00:17:34,697 --> 00:17:36,895
Look how far we've come. We'll figure this out.

312
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:40,098
Right. Yeah. I'll try to stay positive.

313
00:17:40,228 --> 00:17:42,932
No way we just do what the asshole tells us to do.

314
00:17:43,056 --> 00:17:45,507
I mean, come on, use the runts as a proxy?

315
00:17:45,996 --> 00:17:49,981
Send these two runt in to close the deal,
and we might as well lay down a die right now!

316
00:17:51,246 --> 00:17:52,292
Okay, that was rude.

317
00:17:52,496 --> 00:17:54,859
I'm sorry. I'm just pissed off that someone's got us

318
00:17:54,906 --> 00:17:57,281
by the balls. And my friend's lives are in danger?

319
00:17:57,356 --> 00:17:58,552
Forget about it!

320
00:17:58,889 --> 00:18:00,069
We're so gonna die.

321
00:18:01,973 --> 00:18:04,223
I vote we ignore what the jackass wants us to do!

322
00:18:04,306 --> 00:18:06,598
Let's get everyone to the
hospital and forget this happened!

323
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:07,467
Bad idea.

324
00:18:08,266 --> 00:18:12,528
If we are in fact dealing with a man-made
virus, a hospital would be a waste of time.

325
00:18:12,935 --> 00:18:16,064
Not even the most state of the
art ER is be equipped to handle this.

326
00:18:16,306 --> 00:18:17,843
There's no way for them to treat everyone.

327
00:18:18,223 --> 00:18:20,536
We'd be dead before they even figured out what we have.

328
00:18:20,764 --> 00:18:22,046
Seriously?!

329
00:18:22,826 --> 00:18:25,288
I vote we focus on easing the symptoms for now.

330
00:18:25,758 --> 00:18:27,672
You'd best start heading to the rendezvous point.

331
00:18:28,384 --> 00:18:29,880
That's the only way, huh?

332
00:18:31,724 --> 00:18:32,994
Our hands are tied.

333
00:18:33,678 --> 00:18:37,182
If Koro-Sensei could move, we might've had a chance.

334
00:18:37,697 --> 00:18:41,464
I'm starting to wish our assassination
attempt hadn't gone as well as it did.

335
00:18:42,643 --> 00:18:45,102
At the end of the day, this
is all happening because of you.

336
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:49,400
Gotta wonder if these kids'll be willing
to surrender their quarry so easily.

337
00:18:50,014 --> 00:18:52,667
One hour. What the hell can we do?

338
00:18:53,982 --> 00:18:55,941
I think I might have a solution.

339
00:18:56,056 --> 00:18:56,496
Uh.

340
00:19:00,845 --> 00:19:03,328
Koro-Sensei? Everything is ready, sir.

341
00:19:03,764 --> 00:19:04,488
Excellent.

342
00:19:04,653 --> 00:19:06,689
